snippet.textDisplay: I have Mexican friends and I hate when some other Mexican puts them on blast with this speaking Spanish stuff. There are Mexicans who have been here for three generations and just because they look very Mexican doesn't mean they speak Spanish. It's like when I go to a bar mitzvah and some jagoff starts talking Yiddish to me. It's like my people came here in the 1920's. Why would I know Yiddish? This guy is from the CA desert. For all you know, his people have been here for generations. So why do certain groups have the expectation of being bilingual when everyone else just gets by knowing one language and no one ever complains?
